  <p class="kicker" style="margin-top:30px">Coldwast</p>
  <h1>About &amp; editorial policy</h1>

  <h2>What this site is</h2>
  <p>Coldwast is an independent collection of original, regularly-updated programming guides. The current focus is the Haskell and Cabal build toolchain, expanding over time into the broader developer stack - build performance, tooling and deployment.</p>

  <h2>About this domain's history</h2>
  <p>The domain <code>coldwa.st</code> was previously a personal Haskell blog. That site is gone; the domain was acquired after it expired and is now an independent programming-resources project under new, separate editorship.</p>
  <p>Because the domain was historically associated with high-quality Haskell/Cabal writing, we continue to publish on those topics - but the guides here are <strong>new, original works</strong>, rewritten for the current toolchain and maintained by the Coldwast editorial team. They are <strong>not</strong> authored by, signed by, or affiliated with the domain's previous owner, and no prior content is reproduced. Where a guide updates a topic the domain once covered, it says so plainly.</p>

  <h2>Editorial honesty</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>No invented benchmarks, ratings, testimonials or "trusted by" claims. Technical statements describe documented, verifiable behaviour of the tools.</li>
    <li>No impersonation. Author identity is the independent Coldwast team, never any individual the domain was formerly linked to.</li>
    <li>Guides are dated and carry a "last updated" date; toolchain facts that have changed since the original era are flagged with their current status.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Affiliate disclosure</h2>
  <p>Some future guides (hosting, deployment, learning resources, tools) may contain affiliate links. When they do, it will be disclosed on the page, links will use <code>rel="sponsored"</code>, and recommendations will reflect genuine technical merit - never paid placement that distorts the advice. No affiliate relationship influences the technical content.</p>

  <p class="meta"><a href="/e/">All guides</a> · <a href="/e/rss.xml">RSS</a></p>
  </div>
</Base>
